pulltitle: improve test framework, add some more tests
pullsbody:
I don't know if this it too much for one pull request. I can break it up into parts (the refactor and the tests for "blush this").
I was also going to add some tests making sure opening a private browsing window worked, but it turns out there's a conflict with panels and private windows (see bug 816257).
There are yet more tests to write (and certainly as we add functionality), but I thought it would be good to just start with this.

pulltitle: implement issue #12 (why can't I just attach this request to that issue?)
pullsbody:
Two issues with this (I'll file them as follow-ups)
1. Using Panel asserts like crazy for some reason. This appears to be a known bug in the add-on sdk: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=811837
2. Clicking "Use Normal Window" needs to whitelist a host, really, not a URL. This should be fixed when we identify blushy sites based on hosts instead of substrings.
pull_repo_desc: A Firefox addon to make private browsing mode more usable.
pull_commit_message: issue 12: hook consent panel into bpUI.handleNavigation

pulltitle: WIP private browsing mode windows work re #1
pullsbody:
Nits:
- pb mode window doesn't open a tab with the 'pb mode explaination text'
  in it.
- re-open a p-b mode window doesn't activate it to the front.
- it takes a long time for the newly opened window to get the 'mask'
  chrome annotation.
pull_repo_desc: A Firefox addon to make private browsing mode more usable.
pull_commit_message:
WIP private browsing mode windows work re #1

Nits:

* pb mode window doesn't open a tab with the 'pb mode explaination text'
in it.
* re-open a p-b mode window doesn't activate it to the front.
* it takes a long time for the newly opened window to get the 'mask'
chrome annotation.
